      "text": "From the 16th to 20th centuries many Fulani communities settled in the highlands of the [[Jos Plateau]], the [[Western High Plateau]] of Bamenda, and [[Adamawa Plateau]] of Nigeria and the Cameroons. These are the highest elevated places in West Africa, and their altitude can reach up to 8,700 feet above sea level. "
