    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "d8d3cbc5dd11528f",
      "text": "The highland plateaus have a more temperate climate conducive for cattle herding activities, which allowed Fulbe populations to settle there in waves of migrations from further west. Though most Fula now live in towns or villages, a large proportion of the population is still either fully nomadic, or semi-nomadic in nature."
